If NodeRepositoryNode will be used to serialize to JSON, I suggest adding a method
@JsonGetter("reports")
public Map<...> getReportsOrNull() { return reports; }

that will be used by jackson to serialize, while our code will typically refer to the getReports() to avoid having to deal with null.

